  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Nataraja
  description: 'Period   : Chola Dynasty (11th Century CE)



    Material: Bronze



    The
    Nataraja represents Lord Shiva performing the cosmic dance (Ananda Tandava).
    Chola bronze sculptures are celebrated for their exceptional craftsmanship, graceful
    form, and spiritual symbolism. This masterpiece is one of the greatest achievements
    of Tamil heritage and South Indian art.'
