  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Lord Krishna
  description: 'Period: Medieval South India


    Material: Bronze


    This bronze
    statue represents Lord Krishna, the divine flute player and the eighth incarnation
    of Lord Vishnu. The sculpture reflects the excellence of South Indian metal casting
    traditions and symbolizes peace, devotion, and spiritual wisdom. Such bronze
    icons were worshipped in temples and carried during religious processions.'
