  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Clay Storage Pot
  description: "Period: chola  Period (Approx. 6th Century BCE \u2013 3rd Century
    CE)\r\n\r\nMaterial: Baked Clay (Terracotta)\r\n\r\nThis clay pot is inspired
    by pottery discovered  in Tamil Nadu. It was used for storing water, grains,
    oil, and food. These artifacts provide evidence of the advanced lifestyle, craftsmanship,
    and culture of the ancient Tamil people during the chola  period."
