  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 506d87980479a9c41b46f67c5c3140bc, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Stone Inscription
  description: 'Period: Chola Dynasty (12th Century CE)



    Material: Granite
    Stone



    This stone inscription records royal orders, temple donations, land
    grants, and administrative details issued during the Chola period. These inscriptions
    were engraved in Tamil and served as permanent historical records. They provide
    valuable information about the governance, economy, religion, and daily life
    of the Chola Empire, making them an important source for understanding South
    Indian history.'
